{
  "texts": [
    "The fragments obtained as a result of the fragmentation process should not be too large, which would cause information weakness.",
    "Likewise, they should not be too small, which would increase exhaustive overhead.",
    "To obtain optimal fragmentation, the following rules must be followed:• Completeness: The data should not be lost during the fragmentation process.",
    "• Reconstruction: If the data is corrupted, it can still be merged without any changes to the data structure.",
    "For all n fragments: fragment 1 þ fragment 2:::fragment n ¼ data • Discreteness: The data in one fragment should not be included in other fragments to avoid data duplication."
  ]
}